&lt;h1 class="relative group">Greeting and Culture
&lt;div id="greeting-and-culture" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#greeting-and-culture" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>What we know, that is because of our efforts &lt;br>
and the support of family and friends.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>What we earn, that is because of our luck and work.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>How do we greet and treat others? It is because of culture.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Namaste, Namaskar, Vanakam, Namaskara, Namaskaram, Om and Ram Ram Ji &lt;br>
is many millennial Indian culture of greeting. &lt;br>
&amp;ldquo;Hi&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Good Morning&amp;rdquo; is western culture. &lt;br>
There is nothing called cosmic or universal culture. &lt;br>
Choose when you greet, go slow and know what you mean.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Why Do We Do Namaste?</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/why-do-we-do-namaste/</link><pubDate>Sun, 02 Jan 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/why-do-we-do-namaste/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5178-Why-Do-We-Do-Namaste.jpg" alt="Why Do We Do Namaste?" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">Why Do We Do Namaste?
&lt;div id="why-do-we-do-namaste" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#why-do-we-do-namaste" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 class="relative group">Meaning of Namaste
&lt;div id="meaning-of-namaste" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#meaning-of-namaste" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Namaste means, I bow down to you.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Normally, you can bow down to some because that person is powerful. Or, out of her/his power, either she/he can give or punish you. So out of that fear you do Namaste. This is Vyapar Drushti. My business will lose if I don&amp;rsquo;t pay my due.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>The Meaning Of Namaste</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/the-meaning-of-namaste/</link><pubDate>Sun, 24 Mar 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/the-meaning-of-namaste/</guid><description>&lt;p>
&lt;figure>
&lt;img class="my-0 rounded-md" loading="lazy" src="https://dasarpai.github.io/assets/images/wiapost/5094-The-Meaning-Of-Namaste.jpg" alt="The Meaning Of Namaste" />
&lt;/figure>
&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">The Meaning Of Namaste
&lt;div id="the-meaning-of-namaste" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#the-meaning-of-namaste" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>“नम्” धातु + ङे प्रत्यय = नम:+ते= नमस्ते &lt;br>
नम् means bow down &lt;br>
ते means to you or for you&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Why should I bow down to you? &lt;br>
Because you are senior to me? &lt;br>
Elder to me? More knowledgeable than me? &lt;br>
Higher in Ashrma to me? &lt;br>
Wealthier than me? &lt;br>
Powerful than me?”&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>